        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 6 at 3:59PM PDT by NWS Medford OR</headline>
        <description>At 359 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Scott Bar, or 17 miles east of Happy Camp, moving northwest at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Seiad Valley, Jones Beach Picnic Area, Indian Scotty Campground, and
Scott Bar.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
